result.execSummary:
The defendant Anthony R Davis was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Possession of Child Pornography, a class D felony, Wisconsin Statutes 948.12(1m).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

Defendant Anthony R Davis in court, in custody, with Attorney Erik I Colque.   Brian J Juech appeared for the State of Wisconsin.
Court inquires if the parties reviewed the presentence.   Parties have reviewed the information, defendant indicates he did not read the entire document.   Defendant indicates there are no corrections to be made.
Parties stipulate to 10 images.  Defendant stipulates that seized items are to be forfeited to Waukesha Police Department.  
Sentencing recommendations are made.

Court orders the following:   Ct. 2
- Total sentence: 6 years (Initial Confinement: 3 years, Extended Supervision: 3 years)  CREDIT TIME OF 175 DAYS.
- Defendant NOT eligible for Challenge Incarceration 
- Defendant NOT eligible for Substance Abuse Program. 
- Court Costs totaling:     268.00    to be paid as a Condition of Extended Supervision. 
- Surcharge totaling  $5,000.00      to be paid as a Condition of Extended Supervision.
- DNA Surcharge totaling  $250.00   to be paid as a Condition of Extended Supervision.
- Conditions of Extended Supervision: Psychological Evaluation and follow through.  Maintain absolute sobriety. Disclose to any physician your drug history/dependency.  Submit to an AODA assessment and follow through with any treatment/counseling.  Follow thru with any treatment/counseling recommended by Agent. Maintain full-time employment and/or school.
